@page "/about"
@{
  ViewData["Title"] = "About - Queenzone";
  ViewData["Description"] = "About Queenzone, the restored archive of Queenzone.com.";
  ViewData["CanonicalPath"] = "/about";
}

<partial name="_PageHero" model='@(("About", "Queenzone", "The restored archive of Queenzone.com, preserving its news, articles, photography and community history.", ""))' />

<section class="qz-section qz-section--warm">
  <div class="qz-container" style="max-width: var(--container-text);">

    <p class="lede">Queenzone is an archive of Queenzone.com, restored so that its public history can be found, read and enjoyed again.</p>

    <p>Queenzone began at the end of 1995 as <strong>Richard's Queen Page</strong>, a small fan site that grew into a long-running home for Queen news, articles, photography and community discussion. The original site was retired in 2020.</p>

    <p>With the help of modern tools, and with AI making this kind of careful restoration far more enjoyable, I decided to bring the public archive back to life. I no longer have the original Queenzone.com domain, so the archive now lives here at Queenzone.org.</p>

    <p>The goal is simple: preserve the useful public material from the old site, make it easier to explore, and keep it available for Queen fans who still remember the place - and for those discovering it for the first time.</p>

    <p>Regards,<br>
      <strong>Richard Orchard</strong><br>
      <a href="https://www.richardorchard.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.richardorchard.com</a>
    </p>

  </div>
</section>
